{{Infobox artwork|title=The Meeting of Frederick II and Joseph II in Neisse in 1769|image=Adolph_Menzel_-_Begegnung_mit_Kaiser_Joseph_II_in_Neiße_1769.jpg|year=1855-1857|artist=Adolph Menzel|museum=Alte Nationalgalerie|city=Berlin|height_metric=247|width_metric=318|medium=oil on canvas}}
'''''The Meeting of Frederick II and Joseph II in Neisse in 1769''''' is an 1855-1857 history painting by [[Adolph Menzel]], showing the meeting of [[Frederick II of Prussia]] with [[Joseph II, Holy Roman Emperor]] at [[Nysa, Poland|Neisse]] on 25 August 1769. It is now in the [[Alte Nationalgalerie]] in Berlin.

{{Adolph Menzel}}

